27/01/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Justice Minister Cemil Cicek said Wednesday (26 January) that legal proceedings are under way to request the extradition of KONGRA-GEL leader Remzi Kartal from Germany. 
Kartal was arrested at the weekend in southern Germany for suspected membership in a terrorist organisation. 
Meanwhile, KONGRA-GEL has claimed responsibility for a fire that destroyed a warehouse of near Istanbul, causing over $5m in damages. 
The group is threatening further attacks.
On Thursday, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan meets with German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder at the World Economic Forum in Davos. 
The talks will focus on Turkey's bid for EU membership and on efforts to reunify Cyprus. 
(NTV, AFP - 26/01/05)
